#SQL injection UNION attacks
  UNION SQL Injection me attacker UNION keyword use karke original query ke sath dusri query ka data bhi nikal leta hai.
Isse database ke dusre tables ka sensitive data (username, password, email) access ho sakta hai.
Example:
SELECT a,b FROM table1 UNION SELECT c,d FROM table2
Bachav ke liye input validation aur prepared statements use karte hain.

UNION attack tabhi kaam karta hai jab dono queries me same number of columns ho.
Saath hi columns ka data type compatible hona chahiye (text ke jagah text, number ke jagah number).
Attack karne ke liye pehle attacker check karta hai ki original query kitne columns return kar rahi hai.
Fir wo dekhte hai kaunsi column injected data ko show kar sakti hai.

#Determining the number of columns required
UNION attack ke liye pehle pata karna padta hai ki query me kitne columns hain.

Iske liye attacker ORDER BY use karta hai:

' ORDER BY 1--
' ORDER BY 2--
' ORDER BY 3--
Jab column number limit se zyada hota hai, database error deta hai.
Error ya response change dekhkar attacker samajh jata hai ki total kitne columns return ho rahe hain.
Example:-
http://example.com/products?id=5' ORDER BY 1--
http://example.com/products?id=5' ORDER BY 2--

Dusra method: UNION SELECT NULL payloads se columns ka number check karna.

Example:

' UNION SELECT NULL--
' UNION SELECT NULL,NULL--
' UNION SELECT NULL,NULL,NULL--
Agar NULLs ka number original query ke columns se match nahi karta → error aata hai.
NULL har data type me compatible hota hai → column type mismatch ka problem nahi.
Jab NULLs ka number match karta hai → database extra row return karta hai (sab NULL values ke saath).
HTTP response me effect alag ho sakta hai: extra row dikh sakti hai, error aa sakta hai, ya response same reh sakta hai.

