#Database-specific syntax
Oracle database me har SELECT query me FROM clause chahiye.

Matlab: SELECT something alone kaam nahi karega, table ya dual specify karni padti hai.

Example:

' UNION SELECT NULL FROM DUAL--

→ DUAL ek dummy table hai, sirf Oracle me use hota hai.

MySQL me FROM compulsory nahi hota agar simple expressions return kar rahe ho.
Comments (-- ya #):
SQL injection me original query ke baad ka part ignore karne ke liye use hota hai.
MySQL: -- (space zaruri) ya #
Oracle: -- (space optional)

#Finding columns with a useful data type
Goal: SQL injection me wo column find karna jo string data store kar sake.
Process:
Pehle column count pata karo.

Fir har column me ek string try karo using UNION SELECT:

' UNION SELECT 'a',NULL,NULL,NULL--
' UNION SELECT NULL,'a',NULL,NULL--
' UNION SELECT NULL,NULL,'a',NULL--
' UNION SELECT NULL,NULL,NULL,'a'--
Agar column string compatible hai → extra row ya response me string dikhegi.
Agar error aata hai (jaise varchar to int conversion failed) → wo column number compatible nahi hai.
Tip: Jo column string accept karta hai, wahi aage sensitive data retrieve karne ke liye use hota hai.


